:::summary
Athens was the cultural and intellectual heart of ancient Greece — birthplace of democracy, philosophy, drama, and the Western intellectual tradition. Home to Socrates, Plato, Aristotle, Pericles, and the Parthenon, Athens in the 5th and 4th centuries BC produced an explosion of ideas that still shape law, science, literature, and thought across the entire Western world.
